But which of them could ever yet ga ther a church to live according to their ordinaunces: And yet our Prophetes have had the most ercellent and re nowned common weales, or congre gations, yea and that more is, the most flourishing kingdomes in al the world under their authoritie. All the wise men in the whole worlde, I meane those which lived in this time, did re verence Salomon, a ling and so great
a Prophet, and came unto him from
the very outmost endes of the worlde.
Daniel also had the preminence a
mong the wise men at Babylon, being
then the most renowned Monarchie
in all the worlde.
He was moreover in great estima
tion with Darius Medus, the sonne of
Astiages or Assuerus , and also with
Cyrus that most excellent king. And
here it liketh me well to speake some
what of that divine forelnowledge in
our Prophetes, and most allured fore
shewing of things which were to come
after many yeeres passed. And now to
say nothing of others, did not Claias
most truely foretel those things which
were afterward fulsilled by the Jewes
in our Lord Christ: Not in vaine did
he seeme to them of old time to bee ra
ther an Evangelist than a Prophet
foretelling things to come. Hee did o
penly tell the name of king Cyrus one
hunored and threescore yeeres at the
least, before that Cyrus was borne.
Daniel also, was called of them in the
olde time, by the name of one which
knewe much. For, hee did foretel
those things which are, and have been
done in all the kingooms of the world
almost, and among the people of God,
from his owne time untill the time of
Christ, and further untill the last day
of judgement, so plainely that hee may
seeme to have compiled an historie of
those thinges, which then were alrea
dy gone and past. All these thinges
I say, doe very evidently prove, that
the docrine, and writings of the Pro
phets are the very word of God: with
which name and title they are set
foorth in sundrie places of the Scrip
tures. Verily, Peter the Apostle say
eth, The prophecie came not in olde
time by the wil of man: but holy men
of God spake as they mere moved by
